summary:
The Security Council,

Condemning violence against UN personnel in peacekeeping operations, 
Paying tribute to those who have sacrificed their lives, 
Underscoring peacekeeping's role in maintaining international peace and security, 

 Recognizes need to raise awareness on mental health and psychosocial support for UN peace operations personnel; 
Encourages troop- and police-contributing countries and UN Secretariat to provide mental health services during pre-deployment training; 
Fosters a culture of well-being and care during deployment; 
Provides peace operations personnel with adequate mental health and psychosocial support services post-deployment; 
Requests Secretary-General to report on implementation of 2018 UN Mental Health and Well-Being Strategy.
